The paper uses a Takagi-Sugeno fuzzy inference system optimized by neural network learning and evolutionary computation to model the complex export pattern behavior of multinational corporation subsidiaries. This involves machine learning, optimization, and fuzzy logic, which are all relevant to the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), neural networks (cs.NE), swarm intelligence (cs.SI), and computational engineering (cs.CE).
